From: Cline (audit B1) <audit@ask>
Date: Tue, 05 May 2026 10:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fmlib: align t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams with kernel UAPI (drop dead `shared` field)

This is finding F01 from plans/audit/AUDIT-fmlib.md (the load-bearing
ABI defect behind every prior dpa_app SIGSEGV cascade).

01-mono-ask-extensions.patch added `bool shared` to userspace
t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams (include/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h:1720) but
the matching kernel struct ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t (release/
patches/kernel/sdk-sources/include/uapi/linux/fmd/Peripherals/
fm_pcd_ioctls.h:1233-1285) was NEVER extended.

src/fm_lib.c::FM_PCD_KgSchemeSet does:

    ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t params;
    memcpy(&params, p_Scheme, sizeof(t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams));

Userspace t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams is one bool (1 byte + alignment) larger
than kernel ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t. The memcpy:

  (a) overruns the kernel struct (writes past end of `params` on the
      stack) by sizeof(bool)+padding bytes, and
  (b) shifts EVERY field after `id` by sizeof(bool)+padding so that
      kernel reads `alwaysDirect`, `netEnvParams`, `useHash`,
      `keyExtractAndHashParams`, `bypassFqidGeneration`, `baseFqid`,
      `numOfUsedExtractedOrs`, `extractedOrs[]`, `nextEngine`,
      `kgNextEngineParams`, `schemeCounter`, `id` from the wrong
      offsets — corrupting handles, FQIDs, and engine selectors.

A grep across both nxp-fmlib/ and nxp-fmc/ shows ZERO writes or reads
of the `.shared` field anywhere in userspace; it was added by 01- but
never actually used. This makes removal safe (no behaviour change) and
restores byte-for-byte layout parity with kernel UAPI, which is the
invariant required by the memcpy in FM_PCD_KgSchemeSet.

Layout invariant after this patch:

  sizeof(t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams) == sizeof(ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t)

If a future "shared scheme" feature is required, it must be tracked in
a sibling user-space struct that does NOT live inside the ioctl
payload, or added to the kernel UAPI side first (with a UAPI bump and
matching producer-side fixes/ patch).

A static_assert tripwire is added in fm_lib.c so any future drift
between the two struct layouts becomes a compile-time error rather
than another silent run-time corruption.

Audit reference: plans/audit/AUDIT-fmlib.md F01, F02
Closes: dpa_app SIGSEGV cascade root cause

Signed-off-by: Cline <audit@ask>
---
diff -urN a/include/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h b/include/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h
--- a/include/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h	2026-05-05 10:00:00.000000000 +0000
+++ b/include/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h	2026-05-05 10:00:01.000000000 +0000
@@ -1717,7 +1717,6 @@
         uint8_t                         relativeSchemeId;       /**< if modify=FALSE:Partition relative scheme id */
         t_Handle                        h_Scheme;               /**< if modify=TRUE: a handle of the existing scheme */
     } id;
-    bool                                shared;           /**< This scheme is  shared */
     bool                                alwaysDirect;           /**< This scheme is reached only directly, i.e. no need
                                                                      for match vector; KeyGen will ignore it when matching */
     struct {                                                    /**< HL Relevant only if alwaysDirect = FALSE */
diff -urN a/src/fm_lib.c b/src/fm_lib.c
--- a/src/fm_lib.c	2026-05-05 10:00:00.000000000 +0000
+++ b/src/fm_lib.c	2026-05-05 10:00:01.000000000 +0000
@@ -685,6 +685,13 @@
 
     _fml_dbg("Calling...\n");
 
+    /* B1/F01 tripwire: t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams and ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t
+     * MUST have identical layout because the memcpy below treats them as
+     * interchangeable. If a future change to either struct breaks this
+     * invariant, fail at compile time rather than silently corrupting every
+     * KgSchemeSet ioctl payload at run time. */
+    _Static_assert(sizeof(t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams) == sizeof(ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t),
+                   "t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams must match ioc_fm_pcd_kg_scheme_params_t layout (audit F01)");
     memcpy(&params, p_Scheme, sizeof(t_FmPcdKgSchemeParams));
     params.id = NULL;